{"TopicId":76926,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"[1.1] BDArmory v0.11.0.1 (\u002Bcompatibility, fixes) - Apr 23","CreatedByName":"BahamutoD","CreatedById":72433,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-08T00:44:17Z","PageNum":291,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"BahamutoD","CreatedById":72433,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T14:46:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222493598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459764635\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022100708\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pigwig456\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, pigwig456 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmazing work!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a modding question, how did you make the flir targeter have that holo effect, it changes colour based on the direction you look at it from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made the transparent texture color one color (bluish), and the specular color another color (purple ish), then adjust the specular glossiness so it will be blue unless the light is reflecting almost directly to the camera.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222493482\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459752056\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269310\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022inigma\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, inigma said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, here is our first modern dogfight in BDArmory. Thanks @BahamutoD for an amazing series of mods you have put out, making this totally possible!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat battle! \u00A0I\u0027m glad you and Jr. are enjoying it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222493408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459747025\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002288039\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YauS\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, YauS said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the problem of abnromal render of radar images. Original code only consider the Red color channel. Fix it by consider green color channel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/yaus/BDArmory/commit/0cba1a56155b40d312ff493184672567539e857f\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/yaus/BDArmory/commit/0cba1a56155b40d312ff493184672567539e857f\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would probable work as a quick fix, but the pink color in the radar image indicates there\u0027s an issue with the material/shader. \u00A0Thankfully the new part tools for 1.1/U5\u00A0can create asset bundles where I can store custom shaders more reliably. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222493701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459771735\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002267109\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022War Eagle 1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, War Eagle 1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhey Baha\u2026.why not consider incorporating vessel switcher into BDA sense VS pretty much needs BDA to operate?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was kind of an excercise on making a separate mod that is dependent on BDA, and I decided to keep it separate since in the future, it could be considered a cheat tool when we start getting into contracts/careers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"inigma","CreatedById":69310,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T14:48:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/72433-bahamutod/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002272433\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/72433-bahamutod/\u0022\u003E@BahamutoD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0enhancement request: a Carrier Launch slider for the AI pilot, indicating number in seconds when brakes should be released (so plane can throttle up and be launched from a carrier).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BahamutoD","CreatedById":72433,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T14:50:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/69310-inigma/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002269310\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/69310-inigma/\u0022\u003E@inigma\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0That\u0027s a good idea. \u00A0The new wheels in 1.1 are a bit too slippery at the moment though - throttling up will make you start sliding even if the brakes are on\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"War Eagle 1","CreatedById":67109,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T16:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny chance in the future ground vehicles will get an AI function to just move around on their own?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V8jester","CreatedById":136093,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T16:52:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222494102\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459787140\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002267109\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022War Eagle 1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, War Eagle 1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny chance in the future ground vehicles will get an AI function to just move around on their own?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if Mechjeb\u0027s rover auto pilot, coupled with BDA\u0027s\u00A0guard mode would provide the desired result?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YauS","CreatedById":88039,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T16:52:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I using RIM to shoot down a cluster of\u00A0cruiser missile. It always shoot down one of it only. What is it going on?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"War Eagle 1","CreatedById":67109,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T16:54:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222494158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459788728\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136093\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022V8jester\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, V8jester said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if Mechjeb\u0027s rover auto pilot, coupled with BDA\u0027s\u00A0guard mode would provide the desired result?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit might but i don\u0027t use mechjeb so i wouldn\u0027t know.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BahamutoD","CreatedById":72433,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T19:24:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPrerelease Update 2\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA new prerelease version for KSP1.1pre is now ready for testing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChanges:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022padding-left:2em;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;color:rgb(51,51,51);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, \u0027Segoe UI\u0027, Arial, freesans, sans-serif, \u0027Apple Color Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Symbol\u0027;font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:25.6px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nLoad custom shaders via AssetLoader (fixes radar shader bug)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGrab it here:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/BahamutoD/BDArmory/releases/tag/v0.11.0pre2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/BahamutoD/BDArmory/releases/tag/v0.11.0pre2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DuoDex","CreatedById":107061,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T19:35:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222494102\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459787140\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002267109\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022War Eagle 1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, War Eagle 1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny chance in the future ground vehicles will get an AI function to just move around on their own?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes! Would be excellent for tank battles or combined arms assaults.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222494165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459788868\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002267109\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022War Eagle 1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, War Eagle 1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit might but i don\u0027t use mechjeb so i wouldn\u0027t know.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably not, MJ is rudimentary at best and I haven\u0027t had the best of luck with guard on tank turret.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"inigma","CreatedById":69310,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-04T23:36:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOpening up a perpetual challenge here and inviting those brave enough to take title to King of the Hill:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/136016-the-air-supremacy-challenge-king-of-the-hill-bdarmory-2v2-ai-battles/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-04T23:36:52Z\u0022 title=\u002204/04/2016 11:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 4, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by inigma\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YauS","CreatedById":88039,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-05T06:53:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is possible to lock multiple target by radar?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sashan","CreatedById":98897,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-05T07:22:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222494452\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459797882\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002272433\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BahamutoD\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, BahamutoD said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPrerelease Update 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBtw, can you look at how PilotAssistant implements auto throttling? It keeps the plane at the\u00A0required speed precisely, while wing commander makes it oscillate forward and backward.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Penkover","CreatedById":158796,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-05T18:08:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, i have little big problem with firing misseles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHOW ???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI built plane and ship , put the ship in guard\u00A0mode , launch the planer and...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ship is firing only from guns and i am rying to fire missel but it cant hit , i dnt know how to lock target ???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Doctor Dimension","CreatedById":161256,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-06T03:37:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow does one utilize the island airstrip?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YauS","CreatedById":88039,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-06T03:50:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222496395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459879695\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158796\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Penkover\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Penkover said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, i have little big problem with firing misseles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHOW ???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI built plane and ship , put the ship in guard\u00A0mode , launch the planer and...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ship is firing only from guns and i am rying to fire missel but it cant hit , i dnt know how to lock target ???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease enable Debug Label and screen capture. It may caused by shader problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Combatsmithen","CreatedById":146407,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-06T11:07:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222497483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459913846\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Doctor Dimension\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Doctor Dimension said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow does one utilize the island airstrip?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook up kerbinside\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ckirky","CreatedById":150614,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-06T13:13:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbug in 1.1 pre release (steam)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNODAR radar appears but\u00A0nothing else\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhelp?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfixed it, the second download has the parts, the first just has a load of CS files, why?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfixed is generalistic\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nloaded up fine, went into the SPH and saw the BDA tab, game froze and i saw that there as\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E5\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0BDA tabs, then the game crashed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nagain, WHY?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIgnore me, last update fixed it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-07T10:18:23Z\u0022 title=\u002204/07/2016 10:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by ckirky\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BahamutoD","CreatedById":72433,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-06T15:40:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPrerelease Update 3\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/BahamutoD/BDArmory/releases/tag/v0.11.0pre3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/BahamutoD/BDArmory/releases/tag/v0.11.0pre3\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Fix hidden cursor on vessels without weapon manager\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-06T15:40:49Z\u0022 title=\u002204/06/2016 03:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 6, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by BahamutoD\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"andreasblom","CreatedById":133693,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-07T17:01:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs a jernas\u00A0turret w/ guns possible in bda? (Think tungaska)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-07T17:02:12Z\u0022 title=\u002204/07/2016 05:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by andreasblom\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFuggin oddogorrect\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"War Eagle 1","CreatedById":67109,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-07T21:35:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222500426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460048468\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133693\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022andreasblom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, andreasblom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs a jernas\u00A0turret w/ guns possible in bda? (Think tungaska)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"War Eagle 1","CreatedById":67109,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T01:46:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan we have a button in the weapon manager that lets us prioritize air or ground targets?\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat way things like AA guns don\u0027t act as rapid firing tanks or so that attacker type aircraft won\u0027t go for enemy fighters first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"colmo","CreatedById":25950,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T14:41:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222501428\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460080007\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002267109\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022War Eagle 1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, War Eagle 1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan we have a button in the weapon manager that lets us prioritize air or ground targets?\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat way things like AA guns don\u0027t act as rapid firing tanks or so that attacker type aircraft won\u0027t go for enemy fighters first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is something that could be governed per weapon too. An Abrahms M1 turret, because it is long range, always gets selected over a chaingun turret, even though it will never, ever, succeed in shooting down an aircraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Volt","CreatedById":4686,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T15:33:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPhys load distance possibly not working again in the latest 1.1 Prerelease? My planes are loading in at mostly random distances 5-10km while set at 40k phys load. Anyone else getting this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, I\u0027m getting a lot of weird behaviour. AI refuse to fire - that may be me never having used the fight system before - and they make excessive use of rudder, sliding back and forth between max left sideslip and max right. I\u0027m doing something wrong here, I\u0027m sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReproduction steps seem simple... activate guard mode, activate standby pilot, change teams, spawn at a different base, fly towards the planeplanes. Do they load in at the distance set? Do they engage? Am I an idiot?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-08T15:47:00Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2016 03:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Volt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Melfice","CreatedById":3143,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T15:49:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222502462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002276926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460129584\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00224686\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Volt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Volt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPhys load distance possibly not working again in the latest 1.1 Prerelease? My planes are loading in at mostly random distances 5-10km while set at 40k phys load. Anyone else getting this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre the planes landed.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf I recall correctly, anything landed doesn\u0027t load until 10 kilometres away. This is hardcoded to avoid catastrophes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Volt","CreatedById":4686,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T15:51:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, yes, they are landed. Is it even possible to set up planes patrolling outside those 10km at the moment before launching your own interceptor? Gotta love game limitations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA video speaks a thousand words, so here\u0027s a video of what I\u0027m seeing for you:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/ykYB5NgkiGo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs you can see neither aircraft is making an attempt to switch weapons and acquire the other. And yes, the other one is set to team A. The rudder wobble is visible near the end.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-08T16:09:44Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2016 04:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Volt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}